parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the vehicle to shake, pulsate, or vibrate when braking, leading to extended stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
Brake system failure can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Steering system failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
Engine and electrical system issues can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience other problems, leading to accidents or injuries.
Throttle linkage issues can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Accelerator pedal sticks to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Passlock system can cause the vehicle to stall or refuse to start, leaving the driver stranded and vulnerable to potential safety risks.

the fuel supply is cut off
